    <task id="LOCAL-00025" summary="quietly broke any table where the extractor emitted entries out of their                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               &#10;  original sub-entry order.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            &#10;                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         &#10;  battle-menu.txt triggered it: the extractor placed entry :0 at file                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    &#10;  position 17 (because entry 0's data pointer sorts after entries 1-17 in the                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            &#10;  ROM's original layout). Every sub-entry in the battle region of                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        &#10;  meta-table entry 0 ended up off-by-one — sub 33's slot received                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      &#10;  battle-menu entry 0's &quot;select unit&quot; text, while the original sub 33 content                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            &#10;  (the shared &quot;Are you sure?&quot; YES/NO confirmation dialog) landed in sub 32's                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             &#10;  slot.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  &#10;                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         &#10;  Symptom: scenario info screen (e.g. Fusion Temple) showed body text cut off                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            &#10;  after &quot;You're done&quot; with an empty YES/NO prompt box. The shared                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        &#10;  confirmation dialog is loaded from battle-menu sub 33 by the scenario info                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             &#10;  function at $01:EB0F, so every screen that pops a YES/NO confirmation saw                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            &#10;  wrong content once metatbl_battle.asm relocated entry 0 to $C5.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        &#10;                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         &#10;  The fix parses `:(\d+)` from the header, stores entries keyed by that index,                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           &#10;  then emits encoded_entries in range(0, max_idx+1) order, filling any                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   &#10;  missing indices with empty stubs. Falls back to file order if a header has                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             &#10;  no :N component (preserves behavior for any non-conforming tables).                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    &#10;                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         &#10;  Diagnosis notes:                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       &#10;  - TextPtrDispatch and the 3-byte $C5 ptr table were both correct; verified                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             &#10;    by read-breakpoint on $228000-$228257 — hit inside TextPtrDispatch at                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                &#10;    $2E:AA7B with $14/$16 = $C5:$8000 resolving sub 33 to a valid target.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                &#10;  - Phase 1 text buffer at WRAM $0400 contained the full resolved text                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   &#10;    including the tail prompt, but phase 2 rendered only up to &quot;You're done&quot;                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             &#10;    because sub 33's bytes were unrelated data for the renderer to process.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              &#10;  - Byte-level comparison of sub 33 data at $C5:$8E42 vs. original $02:$BE16                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             &#10;    revealed completely different content; the original sub 33 signature                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 &#10;    `FF 15 1A FF 80 04 FF FC 82 00` was found in the new build at $C5:$8DCD                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              &#10;    (sub 32's slot), confirming the off-by-one shift.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    &#10;  - scenario-desc, script, quiz-text, etc. were unaffected because their                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 &#10;    extractions happened to be in natural index order already.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           &#10;                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         &#10;  Minor unrelated observation (not fixed here): battle-menu entry 17 contains                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            &#10;  `[c]` which isn't defined in eng.tbl, so the encoder emits literal ASCII                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               &#10;  `5B 63 5D` instead of the original single byte `$40`. Does not affect the                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              &#10;  metatbl redirect path.">
